OL,3,CCan the UK's first drug consumption
OL,4,Croom reduce Scotland's drug-related
OL,5,Cdeaths?
OL,7,FIf the Scottish government is unable
OL,8,Fto join those dots through this
OL,9,Fservice, it becomes little more than a
OL,10,Fplace to keep people addicted to drugs
OL,11,Falive but without much hope of ever
OL,12,Fknowing a better life.
OL,14,FRight outside where The Thistle will
OL,15,Fopen, we meet Billy.
OL,17,FHe is 42 years old, has been using
OL,18,Fdrugs since he was eight, and is now
OL,19,Fin a wheelchair having lost his leg
OL,20,Ffrom injecting into a wound.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
